description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an efficient Pharmacy Support Worker who already holds an NVQ Level 2 In Pharmacy Services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants will need the above qualification and previous Pharmacy experience in either Hospital or retail Pharmacy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to be organised and able to work under pressure to support our Pharmacy Service to inpatients at St James’ Hospital. The ability to work accurately is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Key duties will include;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Labelling and Dispensing medicines for inpatients following standard operating procedures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Ordering and receipt of Medicines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Stock control and recycling of medicines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Dispensing Controlled Drugs to wards and departments&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will gain experience working at ward level as well as within the inpatient dispensary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a forward thinking department that values the contribution of all our staff. There are opportunities to progress within pharmacy services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;All applications must be made on line.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;For any further information, please contact Lauran Craig at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lauran.craig@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; or on 0113 2066925.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
